        public void updateCharacters()
        Method used to check which characters are still alive. If the hero is alive, add it to the new hero list, and update this.heroes with the new hero list. Repeat for the list of bad guys.

        public void stopGame​(int duration)
        Two options for pausing or stopping the game. Tries pausing the game by putting the thread to sleep for the given duration, catches an interrupted exception and prints the stack trace.
        Parameters:
        duration -

      • stopGame

        public void stopGame()
        Changes status of running to false.

      • startBattle

        public void startBattle()
        Runs for as long as the number of heroes and number of bad guys is above 0. Once one of the teams loses all members, game ends. Runs through each hero and displays the attack that they execute. Then, performs each of the heroes' attacks. Then, performs the bad guys' attacks in response. Updates the character lists at the end of each round.

      • run

        public void run()
        Main game loop We can repeat the loop update() data and repaint() components here. Uses a while loop to run for the duration of the game. Updates and repaints while delta is greater or equal to 1. Reference: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VpH33Uw-_0E
        Specified by:
        run in interface java.lang.Runnable
